sentences.english: When we want to intubate the patient, he turns out to have dentures in his mouth.
sentences.chinese: 当我们想给他插管时，我们发现他的嘴里装有假牙。

sentences.english: Don't want no bright lights, false teeth, doorbells, landlords.
sentences.chinese: 我不想要耀眼的灯光，假牙，门铃，房东。

sentences.english: The wife snaps, "Because I'm waiting for the teeth! ""
sentences.chinese: 老太太咂咂嘴，“我在等他的假牙。”

sentences.english: Don't wear your dentures for a few days until your gum has healed.
sentences.chinese: 牙龈没有好之前，这几天先不要戴假牙。

sentences.english: This false one can almost work as real teeth, but just do not bite bones with them.
sentences.chinese: 假牙基本上象真牙一样好使，只是不能啃骨头。

sentences.english: This is true even if you wear dentures .
sentences.chinese: 这是真的，即使你是带假牙。

sentences.english: It made my dentures very clean and was good tasting as well.
sentences.chinese: 它说了我的假牙也很干净并善于品尝等。

sentences.english: You soak your dentures in coffee overnight.
sentences.chinese: 你把自己的假牙泡在咖啡里过夜。

sentences.english: Great White Dental Lab in Lodi fashions enamel teeth called "crowns."
sentences.chinese: 白色的假牙被洛迪时尚称为“王冠”。

sentences.english: These two sets are in the more southern guard tower of Arkham East.
sentences.chinese: 这两副假牙在阿克汉姆东边那个较靠南边的守卫塔上。

sentences.english: First, denture wearers should make sure that dentures are fitted properly.
sentences.chinese: 首先，假牙佩戴者应该确保正确地安装假牙。

sentences.english: " Chico then says "Well, my last student had a false set of teeth.
sentences.chinese: Chico说“好的，我上个学生有一副假牙。”

sentences.english: Remove the dentures, so as to avoid inhalation of the respiratory tract.
sentences.chinese: 取下假牙，以免误吸入呼吸道。

sentences.english: My false teeth flew out the window on my drive to work.
sentences.chinese: 我开车上班路上，假牙从窗户飞出去了。

sentences.english: I do not have dentures, but I have a clear retainer.
sentences.chinese: 我不戴假牙，但我有一个清晰的家臣。
